# 📚 DSA-Based Library Tracker GUI (C++ & Qt)

This project is a **Graphical User Interface (GUI)** based Library Management System built using **C++** and **Qt Framework**. It demonstrates practical applications of **Data Structures and Algorithms (DSA)** including Binary Search Trees, Stacks, Queues, and Hash Maps.

> 🔧 Designed for desktop use with an intuitive Qt interface.

---

## 🚀 Features

- 📘 **Add New Book** – Store books using a Binary Search Tree (BST)
- 👥 **Borrow Book** – Issue books with a user queue if already borrowed
- 🔄 **Return Book** – Stack-based return logic and automatic reissue to waiting users
- 📚 **View All Books** – Display available and issued books via in-order traversal
- 🧾 **View Borrowed Books** – See currently issued books
- 🖥️ **Modern Qt GUI** – Built with Qt Designer and C++ backend

---

## 🛠️ Technologies Used

| Component       | Description                      |
|----------------|----------------------------------|
| C++             | Core logic and data structures   |
| Qt 6 / 5        | GUI toolkit for interactive UI   |
| MinGW / MSVC    | Compiler (depending on your setup) |
| CMake or qmake  | Build system                     |

